 "faq": [
  {
   "question": "Where does Balance Druid Phase 2 BiS come from?",
   "answer": "From the gear worn by 313 top-ranked Balance Druid DPS parses on Warcraft Logs during Phase 2 (Serpentshrine Cavern and Tempest Keep), aggregated per slot — what high parsers actually equip, not a spreadsheet ideal."
  },
  {
   "question": "What are the highest-consensus Balance Druid items in Phase 2?",
   "answer": "Belt of Blasting (91%), Nordrassil Headpiece (90%), Nordrassil Wrath-Mantle (90%). When an item sits above ~70% among top parsers, treat it as the priority drop to chase."
  },
  {
   "question": "Should I follow this list exactly for Phase 2?",
   "answer": "Use it as a loot-priority guide, not a checklist — expand each slot's alternatives, because second-choice items are often within a few percent and drop from entirely different bosses in Serpentshrine Cavern and Tempest Keep."
  },
  {
   "question": "What gems should a Balance Druid use in Phase 2?",
   "answer": "Chaotic Skyfire Diamond in the meta socket, then Runed Living Ruby, Potent Noble Topaz and Glowing Nightseye in the coloured sockets. Epic gems only arrive with patch 2.4 (Sunwell), so these rare-quality cuts are the ceiling for this phase."
  },
  {
   "question": "What enchants does a Balance Druid need in Phase 2?",
   "answer": "10 slots are worth enchanting. The biggest swings are Glyph of Power on head, Greater Inscription of the Orb on shoulders, Runic Spellthread on legs and Enchant Weapon - Sunfire on main hand. The head and shoulder enchants are consumable items rather than enchanter work — Glyph of Power comes from Almaador — Shattrath City."
  }
 ]
